caption.text:
A bit of flair ✨ 

#UCL #Bellingham

A holiday so truly special cause it’s one with the fam! Taking you through our super relaxed day 1 at @luxsouthari the moment we stepped out of the sea plane and into the property, we were spell bound at how seriously they take Hospitality! The warm smiles and welcoming hugs linger on even after you’ve left and That’s their superpower ✨🫶 we walked on the beach, ate delicioussss Asian dinner at the East Market, took a night dip in our pool overlooking the ocean, while watching the sunset and drinking delicious cocktails 🍸 No better way to have started the holiday! 😍 @pickyourtrail just knows how well to pamper you.

“I have treasured the goat all my life."
 
This pottery goat, which was made by King Charles, has sold for £8,500.
 
The small ceramic animal, which had been kept for 55 years by a Canadian named Raymond Patten, was auctioned in the UK.
 
It was given to him on his 21st birthday by a great aunt who worked as a cook at Cambridge University.
 
Tap the link in our bio to find out the goat’s owner want it to have a new home.
 
(📷 Hansons Auctioneers, Getty Images)

caption.text: on-the-go glow ✨✨🎀 @haileybieber

🗣️ Florentino Perez: „THANK YOU, DEAR TONI KROOS 🤍

┈━═☆ Hala Madrid ☆═━┈

📲 The images and videos used on this account belong to their original owners. If there is any issue, please contact me.

#tonikroos #kroos #realmadrid #ucl #championsleague #laliga #goal #football #futbol #futebol #modric #vinijr #bellingham #ardagüler #madridismo #madridistas #mood #cristiano #cristianoronaldo #valverde #fedevalverde #soccer #halamadrid

A 5-year-old boy named Jordan Marotta, born with one hand, has become the youngest person to receive a bionic arm. He was fitted with an Iron Man-themed ‘Hero Arm’ prosthetic, which allowed him to ride a scooter with both hands. Jordan was overjoyed and quickly adapted to using the prosthetic. His mother, Ashley, had initially been told he was too young for a prosthetic, but Open Bionics agreed to fit him after a successful trial. Jordan’s new arm has given him confidence and enabled him to perform daily activities with ease.
